Reasoning: The paper proposes a new interpretation of measures of information and disorder by connecting these concepts to group theory in a new way. It introduces a combinatorial measure of information and disorder called the integer entropy and shows its relation to the Shannon entropy. The paper also discusses the Cameron-Semeraro cycle polynomial and its use in analyzing the integer entropy for finite groups. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.IT (Information Theory). Other likely sub-categories include cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science).
